## Risk Rating: Critical

Ransomware directly threatens data availability and business continuity. Even scoped to a single host, this rating reflects worst-case blast radius (encryption spreading via shared drives/lateral movement) rather than confirmed current impact — critical severity is standard for any confirmed/suspected active encryption event regardless of scope at time of detection.

## Recommendations

- **Immediate:** Isolate the affected endpoint from the network to halt further encryption/spread.
- Kill the identified malicious process; preserve a memory/disk image before remediation for forensics.
- Verify offline/immutable backup integrity before considering restoration.
- Fleet-wide sweep for the same process hash/behavior signature.
- Restrict SMB/RDP between endpoints where not operationally required (segmentation limits lateral spread in future incidents).
- Review EDR alerting thresholds for mass-file-modification detection — tune for faster time-to-alert.
- Post-incident: rotate credentials used on the affected host, review for initial access vector (phishing, RDP brute-force, exploited service).

## Detection Query Example (KQL)

```kql
DeviceFileEvents
| where ActionType == "FileModified" or ActionType == "FileRenamed"
| summarize FileOps = count() by InitiatingProcessFileName, DeviceName, bin(Timestamp, 5m)
| where FileOps > 100
| order by FileOps desc
```

